Come enjoy a zip lining course covering 1,700 feet worth of cable, consisting of 7 high flying zip line stations and 3 tree-top aerial bridges.  Covering 10 acres, you’ll be cruising at top speed right in the thick of Northeast Florida’s breathtaking natural setting. At the end of your journey, take on the 450-foot Exit Challenge with a partner. Reaching speeds up to 30 MPH, the Exit Challenge is a 1-on-1 test to see who our fastest rider is! Who knows, it could even be you!

This experience also includes primitive camping for one or two nights which provides a great adventure and lasting memories. Each family/troop will provide their own accommodations and food; however, fire pits will be available.  Most importantly, fun patch is included.

*all zip line participants must be at least brownie level and weigh between 65-275 lbs; must be able to comprehend safety instructions and waiver is required
*This event is for 2016 registered Girl Scouts.
*Girl/adult ratios must be followed and adults are expected to stay on the premises during the event.

$60/girl/youth, $60/adult
Contact: Brittany McCallister 904.389.3071
